Subject: Re: [VB] CW crank and flywheel

It's pretty inexpensive to get the old one machined. Might as well make
use of the 8 dowels. Most aftermarket 8 dowels are lightened, not good
for buses as much. For DYI, there is a tool to jig it and drill it, for
like 35.00, or pay a little less at Rimco or elsewhere good.
Al



